subSubSection.paragraph:
Description.
Male: Body length 5, width 3.0. Medium-sized harvestmen with rectangular shaped body. The saddle pattern is clearly distinguishable, along the middle of the pattern is a clearly distinguishable light stripe (
Fig. 1A
). The ocular tubercle is slightly trapezoidal with 9 pairs of black-tipped denticles (
Fig. 1B
). Small denticles are located along the boundaries of tergites. The color of the abdomen is sandy, the back is slightly darker due to the presence of a large number of dark brown spots and various shapes. Legs are of medium length. Leg I = 1.33. Fe I slightly thickened. Lengths of leg segments: I: 4.0 + 1.5 + 3.8 + 4.5 + 6.6 = 20.4; II: 6.5 + 2.0 + 5.4 + 5.6 + 14.0 = 33.5; III: 4.4 + 1.5 + 4.0 + 5.3 + 9.0 = 16.6; IV: 5.8 + 1.6 + 4.5 + 7.4 + 11.6 = 30.9. Femora of all legs longitudinally with small denticles. Chelicera typical for the genus, not thickened, both segments dorsally with black-tipped denticles (
Fig. 1E, F
). Basal cheliceral segment length 1.1, distal segment 2.2. Pedipalp not long, all segments with setae only (
Fig. 1G, H
). Pedipalp segment lengths: 2.6 + 1.1 + 1.5 + 3.0 = 8.2. Penis rather long, base not wide, slightly tapering mid-shaft, then slightly widening again towards tip (
Fig. 1M–P
). “Wings” not widened, glans laterally triangular, with 1 pair of setae. Penis length 3.0, glans 0.3, stylus 0.1.

Female: Larger than male, with rounded body shape (
Fig. 1C
). Female body length 7.0, width 4.0. Leg lengths: I: 3.4 + 1.2 + 2.8 + 3.5 + 6.0 = 10.96, II: 5.2 + 1.2 + 4.5 + 5.0 + 11.6 = 27.5, III: 3.6 + 1.2 + 3.0 + 5.0 + 7.4 = 20.2, IV: 5.0 + 1.5 + 4.0 + 7.0 + 9.6 = 27.1. Pedipalp segment lengths: 1.8 + 1.0 + 1.0 + 2.4 = 6.2 (
Fig. 1K, L
). Female chelicerae have only bristles (
Fig. 1I, J
). Cheliceral basal segment length 1.5, distal segment length 1.9.

Dr. M.V. Nabozhenko (Rostov-on-Don, 
Russia
) kindly provided us with the material on which the description is based.
